      <description>They Don&amp;#8217;t Call it Sin City for Nothing Let&amp;#8217;s be honest. One of the more popular reasons men go to Vegas is for action that doesn&amp;#8217;t take place at a craps table or roulette wheel. And when men are planning &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/vegas-meets-viagra"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/accessrx-blog/Accessrx_Blog-Where_Vegas_Meets_Viagra.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>They Don&#8217;t Call it Sin City for Nothing</strong></p>
<p>Let&#8217;s be honest. One of the more popular reasons men go to Vegas is for action that <em>doesn&#8217;t</em> take place at a craps table or roulette wheel. And when men are planning on a great Vegas vacation, the last thing the want is a problem with their erectile function. Las Vegas and Viagra are two things that just naturally go together. So if you&#8217;re going to Las Vegas with the goal of enjoying some no-strings, recreational sex, here&#8217;s what you need to know.</p>
<div id="attachment_5486" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/craps-table.jpg" rel="lightbox[5485]" title="Where Vegas Meets Viagra"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5486" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/craps-table-300x224.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="224" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Gambling isn&#39;t the only reason many people visit Las Vegas.</p></div>
<p>First, the lecture. Don&#8217;t be stupid: safe sex is the rule, and if you should leave Clark County in pursuit of recreational sex, condoms are mandatory at all legal brothels. They should be mandatory <em>any time</em> you&#8217;re with someone whose history you do not know, so be prepared, and don&#8217;t make exceptions. A sexually transmitted disease is not how you want to remember your Vegas vacation.</p>
<p><strong>Viagra in Vegas</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5487" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/vegas-strip.jpg" rel="lightbox[5485]" title="Where Vegas Meets Viagra"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5487" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/vegas-strip-300x223.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="223" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Just because someone says it&#39;s Viagra doesn&#39;t mean it&#39;s the genuine product.</p></div>
<p>Now, if you have suffered from erectile dysfunction (ED) and worry that it might be a problem while you&#8217;re in Las Vegas, then you&#8217;ll want to be prepared. You&#8217;re better off obtaining Viagra or another ED drug before you leave home. Sure, you can probably find someone on or off the strip willing to sell you a blue pill that looks like Viagra, but if you do you&#8217;re taking a huge risk. Fake Viagra is extremely easy to find, and at best it lightens your wallet without having any effect on your erectile function. At worst, it could contain harmful substances that could ruin your trip to Vegas by forcing a detour to the ER.</p>
<p><strong>Obtaining Viagra Legally in Las Vegas</strong></p>
<p>What if you&#8217;re in Las Vegas and you decide you want to get Viagra the legal way? Well, it&#8217;s just like getting Viagra anywhere else. You&#8217;ll need to find a doctor who will prescribe it for you, and you&#8217;ll need to take your prescription to a pharmacy to get it filled. Unless you happen to know a physician in Las Vegas, you&#8217;ll probably have the best luck if you search for a family practitioner or a urologist, because these two specialties write the majority of prescriptions for ED drugs.</p>
<div id="attachment_5488" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/waiting-room.jpg" rel="lightbox[5485]" title="Where Vegas Meets Viagra"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5488" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/waiting-room-300x211.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="211" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Spending even part of a Vegas vacation in a doctor&#39;s waiting room isn&#39;t much fun.</p></div>
<p>Here is a list of nine Las Vegas-area doctors, the first three of whom are urologists, with the rest being family practitioners. The list comes from <a href="http://weeklyseven.com/health/2012/02/23/top-docs-2012">weeklyseven.com&#8217;s guide to the best medicine in Las Vegas</a>.</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Dr. Claire Elaine Close 702-220-4006 (Urology)</li>
<li>Dr. Steven Bruce Kurtz 702-233-0727 (Urology)</li>
<li>Dr. Michael Peter Verni 702-212-3428 (Urology)</li>
<li>Dr. Rita Bella Chuang 702-818-4734 (Family Practice)</li>
<li>Dr. Michael John Gunter 702-804-5138 (Family Practice)</li>
<li>Dr. Steven Lampinen 702-366-1206 (Family Practice)</li>
<li>Dr. Amy Renee Sparks 702-243-2689 (Family Practice)</li>
<li>Dr. Raji Venkat 702-818-3207 (Family Practice)</li>
<li>Dr. Sanford Franklin White 702-951-3400 (Family Practice)</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>A Legal, Alternative Way to Obtain Viagra</strong></p>
<p>If you should get to Vegas and then decide to visit a physician for a Viagra prescription, what do you do if the doctor can&#8217;t see you till next Friday and you&#8217;re leaving Wednesday? Your best bet is using a secure online facilitator. You will be asked to answer a health questionnaire that will be evaluated by a physician and, when appropriate, will result in a prescription for Viagra.</p>
<p>The best online facilitators ship the same day when you order early enough, and they will give you the option of overnight shipping, which you can have sent to you care of your hotel. Don&#8217;t worry: good online facilitators won&#8217;t ship you a package with labeling advertising what&#8217;s inside. They know to be discreet. Using an online facilitator also frees up a lot of time you would have spent in a waiting room and cooling your heels at a pharmacy.</p>
<div id="attachment_5489" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/man-at-work.jpg" rel="lightbox[5485]" title="Where Vegas Meets Viagra"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5489" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/man-at-work-300x224.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="224" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">You can obtain real Viagra quickly without a traditional doctor&#39;s appointment.</p></div>
<p><strong>Keep it Safe, and Keep it Legal</strong></p>
<p>Going to Las Vegas in search of a good time is hardly unusual. Just don&#8217;t put yourself into a dangerous situation: make sure you always practice safe sex, and if you believe you need Viagra to cope with ED while you&#8217;re there, obtain it only from a licensed physician or a trusted online facilitator with an excellent track record.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested in treating your ED while maintaining your privacy and enjoying the convenience of quick delivery, <a href="http://www.accessrx.com">AccesRx.com</a> is one of the nation&#8217;s top online facilitators and is staffed by excellent customer service representatives as well as U.S.-licensed physicians and pharmacists. <a href="http://www.accessrx.com/viagra/">They also offer overnight shipping</a> and ship the same day on orders received before 3 p.m. Mountain Time. Good luck and enjoy your stay in Sin City!</p>
