      <description>Value Involves More than Just Price Pfizer brings in about $1.6 billion per year in sales of its blockbuster drug Viagra. But Pfizer isn&amp;#8217;t the company that sells Viagra to you. Instead, you have to choose which vendor to purchase &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/buy-viagra-online-cheap"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/accessrx-blog/Accessrx_Blog-Can_You_Buy_Viagra_Online_for_Cheap.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Value Involves More than Just Price</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5514" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 278px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/piggy-bank.jpg" rel="lightbox[5513]" title="Can You Buy Viagra Online for Cheap?"><img class="size-full wp-image-5514" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/piggy-bank.jpg" alt="" width="268" height="244" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">When buying Viagra online, price is not the only thing to consider.</p></div>
<p>Pfizer brings in about $1.6 billion per year in sales of its blockbuster drug Viagra. But Pfizer isn&#8217;t the company that sells Viagra to you. Instead, you have to choose which vendor to purchase the drug from. Of course you want to choose the one that&#8217;s the cheapest, right?</p>
<p>If you are interested in purchasing drugs like Viagra online, you&#8217;re bombarded with options. A Google search on &#8220;buy Viagra online&#8221; returns nearly 88 million search results. Clearly there are plenty of people who want to sell you Viagra, but how do you separate out the counterfeiters and how do you know which price comparisons are valid?</p>
<p><strong>Where to Begin<br />
</strong></p>
<p>You should compare prices based on dosage: though this, too, can be tricky. For example, some pharmacies price 100 mg Viagra tablets the same as 50 mg Viagra tablets. Because of this, many men would rather obtain a prescription for 100 mg tablets even if they only need 50 mg, because they can split the 100 mg tablets in half and effectively get twice the medication for the same price. When you compare Viagra prices online, you&#8217;ll notice that the respected websites don&#8217;t stray too far from the $20 to $25 per pill price you&#8217;ll find at your local pharmacy.</p>
<p><strong>Pfizer on Pricing</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5515" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/pfizer-logo.jpg" rel="lightbox[5513]" title="Can You Buy Viagra Online for Cheap?"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5515" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/pfizer-logo-300x196.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="196" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Pfizer keeps prices of Viagra within a fairly small range.</p></div>
<p>Pfizer, the manufacturer of Viagra, is quite consistent in its pricing. On its own <a href="http://www.pfizer.com/vtprescribers/long/viagra_long.pdf">website</a>, Pfizer lists the average wholesale price in the state of Vermont as $24.52 per pill for 25, 50, and 100 mg tablets. A company called First Databank determines benchmark prices for what pharmacies in the United States are charged by wholesalers. First Databank&#8217;s pharmaceutical market surveys are used by insurance companies and other drug buyers for use in negotiating reimbursement paid to pharmacies by insurers.</p>
<p>First Databank doesn&#8217;t release their average wholesale price data, but pharmacies and online facilitators use the data along with competition data to determine their prices for prescription drugs like Viagra.</p>
<p><strong>Is There a Generic?<br />
</strong></p>
<p>Because Viagra has not gone off-patent yet, generics are not available in the United States, no matter what all those internet ads say.</p>
<p>Right now, Korean drug maker CJ, has a generic version of Viagra called &#8220;Heragra&#8221; ready to go for around $4.25 per pill, but Pfizer recently stated that their patent for the active ingredient in Viagra is valid until 2014. U.S. generic drug manufacturers have not been able to convince courts that the expiration of patent for the compound itself, Sildenafil, on May 17, 2012 should allow production of generics.</p>
<p>Pfizer says that their patent on the use of Sildenafil for the treatment of erectile dysfunction does not expire until May 2014, and so far courts have agreed. Therefore, you won&#8217;t be seeing generic Viagra until at least May 2014.</p>
<p><strong>Counterfeits Are Extremely Common</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5516" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/fake-v-real-viagra.jpg" rel="lightbox[5513]" title="Can You Buy Viagra Online for Cheap?"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5516" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/fake-v-real-viagra-300x279.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="279" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Fake Viagra can look an awful lot like the real thing.</p></div>
<p>While many online ads for &#8220;Viagra&#8221; try to convince you to buy &#8220;herbal&#8221; or &#8220;natural&#8221; Viagra, these compounds do not have the active ingredient in real Viagra, and there is no proof that they work at all. Furthermore, if you find &#8220;real Viagra&#8221; or &#8220;genuine Viagra&#8221; online for just a few dollars per pill, you can bet that they&#8217;re counterfeit, even if you open them up and they look just like the real thing. Viagra is <a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/counterfeit-viagra-cialis-levitra-ultimate-guide">one of the most commonly counterfeited prescription drugs</a>.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, counterfeit drugs are sometimes a problem even with Canadian pharmacies. While people in the United States tend to automatically trust Canadian websites and particularly Canadian pharmacies (since so many U.S. residents cross the border to shop at brick and mortar Canadian pharmacies), there is no simple way to be sure that Canadian pharmacy websites obtain their products from legitimate drug wholesalers or manufacturers, or that they&#8217;re really located in Canada.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re comparing real Viagra made by Pfizer, don&#8217;t expect more than a few dollars&#8217; difference between prices online. You can save some money, but you should also factor in things like shipping options, costs for shipping, and how long it takes to receive your order.</p>
<p><strong>Compare Prices, Look for Certification</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5517" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 228px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/secure-medical-certified1.jpg" rel="lightbox[5513]" title="Can You Buy Viagra Online for Cheap?"><img class="size-full wp-image-5517" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/secure-medical-certified1.jpg" alt="" width="218" height="143" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Look for pharmacies that have passed stringent certification requirements.</p></div>
<p>When you compare prices of Viagra online, try to ensure that you are comparing prices among legitimate websites. Signs that you&#8217;re buying from a legitimate supplier of authenticated Viagra include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Requiring a prescription for Viagra before it can be dispensed</li>
<li>An actual street address (not a P.O. Box) for the website</li>
<li>The promise to sell only FDA-approved medications</li>
<li>The presence of U.S.-certified pharmacists and physicians on staff</li>
<li>Secure Medical Certification seal on the website</li>
<li>Physicians on staff to issue valid prescriptions based on medical history and online questionnaire data</li>
<li>Patient identity and age verified by phone or electronically</li>
</ul>
<p>Once you have narrowed down your selection of providers to those who are legitimately selling actual Viagra manufactured by Pfizer, you&#8217;re ready to compare prices, including shipping costs and options.</p>
<p><strong>Too Good to Be True?</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5518" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/bag-of-fake-viagra.jpg" rel="lightbox[5513]" title="Can You Buy Viagra Online for Cheap?"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5518" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/bag-of-fake-viagra-300x193.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="193" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">You know the old saying about things that seem too good to be true.</p></div>
<p>When it comes to blockbuster drugs like Viagra, the temptation for counterfeiters and scammers is great. That&#8217;s why you find so many sites advertising Viagra (or herbal or &#8220;generic&#8221; Viagra) at cut-rate prices. Legitimate online facilitators and pharmacies won&#8217;t be selling Viagra for a price significantly different from Pfizer&#8217;s average wholesale price of $24 and change. So if you see Viagra for significantly less than that, you can be fairly certain of one of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>What they&#8217;re selling you is not real Viagra</li>
<li>It will probably be ineffective</li>
<li>It could be harmful</li>
<li>They may simply collect your payment and your credit card data and disappear</li>
</ul>
<p>The old cliché about things that appear too good to be true usually are applies especially well to online Viagra sales. The enormous popularity of the drug, the consensus that it is safe when taken as directed, and the inability for U.S. Customs to examine every package coming into the country provides a huge opportunity for scammers and counterfeiters. And even if their website is shut down, you can bet it will pop up under a new domain within a few days or weeks.</p>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested in safely and securely obtaining authenticated Viagra that has been manufactured by Pfizer, be sure to check <a href="http://www.accessrx.com/">AccesRx.com</a>. This U.S.-based online facilitator has been in business since 1998 and is located in Tempe Arizona. AccessRx.com has U.S.-licensed physicians and pharmacists on staff and provides Viagra at competitive prices with super shipping options and same-day shipping on orders received before 3 p.m. Mountain Time.</p>
