    <item>
      <title>Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?</title>
      <link>http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/safe-buy-viagra-online</link>
      <comments>http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/safe-buy-viagra-online#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 24 May 2012 14:51:23 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>mary</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Erectile Dysfunction]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Cialis]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[ED]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[ED drugs]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[erectile dysfunction]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Levitra]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[online pharmacy]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[prescription drug prices]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Viagra]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.accessrx.com/blog/?p=5440</guid>
      <description>All That Annoying Spam Does Pique Our Interest It doesn&amp;#8217;t seem to matter whether you&amp;#8217;re male, female, single, in a relationship, age 18 or age 80: annoying spam messages urging you to buy &amp;#8220;Herbal Breakthrough Formula!&amp;#8221; or &amp;#8220;Viagra + Cialis &amp;#8230; &lt;a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/erectile-dysfunction/safe-buy-viagra-online"&gt;Continue reading &lt;span class="meta-nav"&gt;&amp;#8594;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/accessrx-blog/Accessrx_Blog-Is_It_Safe_to_Buy_Viagra_Online.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>All That Annoying Spam Does Pique Our Interest</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5441" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/email-symbol.jpg" rel="lightbox[5440]" title="Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5441" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/email-symbol-300x295.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="295" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Ugh. Not another email about the wonders of &quot;Herbal Viagra.&quot;</p></div>
<p>It doesn&#8217;t seem to matter whether you&#8217;re male, female, single, in a relationship, age 18 or age 80: annoying spam messages urging you to buy &#8220;Herbal Breakthrough Formula!&#8221; or &#8220;Viagra + Cialis from Canadian Pharmacy!&#8221; flood your email box daily. Fortunately, spam filters keep most of these messages out of your inbox, but have you ever wondered why after years of everyone knowing that these messages are fake they&#8217;re still used so extensively?</p>
<p>The truth is, erectile dysfunction is very common, and what man doesn&#8217;t wonder if maybe this &#8220;generic Viagra&#8221; or &#8220;herbal Viagra&#8221; actually, against all odds, works? An occasional problem getting an erection is a near-universal experience, and many men wonder if it means they&#8217;re losing erectile function and if they should do something about it.</p>
<p>True erectile dysfunction, which is a more persistent problem, affects around 40 million American men of all ages. The man who has never wondered if he&#8217;s at risk for developing erectile dysfunction and who has never hoped that there&#8217;s a safe, cheap, and widely available product that can prevent ED probably doesn&#8217;t exist in an internet-connected world.</p>
<p><strong>Why People Want to Buy Viagra Online</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5442" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 239px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/businessman.jpg" rel="lightbox[5440]" title="Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?"><img class="size-full wp-image-5442" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/businessman.jpg" alt="" width="229" height="296" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">It can be a hassle to take half a day off to visit a doctor.</p></div>
<p>Another reason those ads for &#8220;cheap Viagra&#8221; and other erectile dysfunction treatments resonate with so many men is that buying Viagra online has a great appeal. A lot of men don&#8217;t like going to the doctor with anything short of a severed limb, and they definitely don&#8217;t want to schedule what usually ends up being several hours out of their workday to talk to a doctor about the possibility they might have erectile dysfunction.</p>
<p>Furthermore, the men who do go to the trouble of visiting their physician, pouring out their sexual history, and obtaining a prescription usually do not look forward to taking that prescription to their local pharmacy, where they not only have to face a pharmacy technician, but also risk running into a neighbor, drinking buddy, or Little League parent.</p>
<p>It only makes sense that men want to buy Viagra online. After all, a person&#8217;s sex life and erectile function are very private subjects. Even sharing their concerns with their partner can be difficult. They would much rather be able to go online, answer some health questions, and after a physician reviews their information, receive a prescription that they can fill online and have delivered to their door in a discreet, plain package.</p>
<p><strong>What Customers Should Look For</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5467" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 228px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/secure-medical-certified.jpg" rel="lightbox[5440]" title="Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?"><img class="size-full wp-image-5467" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/secure-medical-certified.jpg" alt="" width="218" height="143" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Look for online facilitators that are Secure Medical Certified.</p></div>
<p>Fortunately, such places exist on the internet. Unfortunately, so do hundreds, if not thousands, of shady websites that exist only to separate vulnerable men from their money by promising products that are ineffective or dangerous. It<em> is</em> safe to buy Viagra online, but only provided you take several necessary precautions to protect your health and your identity.</p>
<p>Any reputable online facilitator should have, in addition to a web address, a real street address (not a P.O. Box) and a real phone number. They should require a prescription in order to dispense Viagra or any other prescription medication, and they should have a strong authenticity program to ensure that the drugs they dispense are the real, name-brand drugs made by major pharmaceutical companies like Pfizer (maker of Viagra).</p>
<p>Reputable U.S. sites selling Viagra online have carefully-developed health questionnaires that customers complete online, and which are then reviewed by U.S.-licensed physicians. If the physician thinks that Viagra (or whatever prescription drug the customer would like) is appropriate given his questionnaire answers, the customer&#8217;s age and address are verified, and a prescription is issued that can be filled on the same website.</p>
<p>Look for online facilitators that are Secure Medical Certified. These sites have to meet strict requirements about customer privacy, security, and quality assurance.</p>
<p><strong>What Customers Should Avoid</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5443" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 310px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/cheap-viagra-screencap.jpg" rel="lightbox[5440]" title="Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?"><img class="size-medium wp-image-5443" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/cheap-viagra-screencap-300x165.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="165" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">If you see this, click elsewhere, or there&#039;s no telling what you&#039;ll receive.</p></div>
<p>Avoid sites that purport to sell &#8220;generic Viagra&#8221; (or generic Cialis or Levitra) because FDA-approved generic versions of these drugs do not yet exist. Also avoid sites that have prices that are significantly lower than what you would pay at your local pharmacy. Prices for drugs like Viagra are set by manufacturers, and there is not a lot of maneuvering room for pharmacies to offer major discounts. Prices will vary to some degree, but if you&#8217;re seeing Viagra for $10 per pill or less, be very wary.</p>
<p>Customers should avoid websites that do not require a prescription in order to dispense prescription drugs. The likelihood of receiving counterfeit drugs is very high, and it&#8217;s possible you could hand over your credit card information and not receive anything in return. Websites that do not have a legitimate street address, that are written in broken English, or that are smothered in American or Canadian flags should also be approached with great caution.</p>
<p><strong>Conclusions on Safety of Buying Viagra Online</strong></p>
<div id="attachment_5445" class="wp-caption alignnone" style="width: 306px"><a href="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/viagra.jpg" rel="lightbox[5440]" title="Is It Safe to Buy Viagra Online?"><img class="size-full wp-image-5445" src="http://www.accessrx.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/viagra.jpg" alt="" width="296" height="120" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Real Viagra is made by Pfizer and lot numbers can be confirmed with the company.</p></div>
<p>The truth is you <em>can</em> buy Viagra online safely. You cannot buy Viagra online safely for a couple of dollars per pill. Expect to pay prices close to those your local pharmacy or a nearby chain pharmacy charges, and expect to answer health questions online before being able to purchase Viagra.</p>
<p>Sites like AccessRx.com and eDrugstore.MD are examples of online facilitators that pass all the tests. These sites have real-world locations in the United States, and have physicians and pharmacists on staff to review customer requests, answer questions, and process orders. And they only contract with U.S.-licensed pharmacies that receive their drugs directly from verified wholesalers or drug manufacturers.</p>
<p>Sites like these have long track records (over a decade in the cases of AccessRx.com and eDrugstore.MD) and use major shippers like FedEx and the U.S. Post Office. They also understand that customers don&#8217;t want the contents of their shipments openly displayed on packaging, and are committed to customer privacy and online security.</p>
<p>Your sexual health is important enough that you don&#8217;t want to entrust it to a spam site that offers &#8220;Viagra&#8221; at cut-rate prices without a prescription. If you want to <a href="http://www.accessrx.com/">try drugs like Viagra</a> for erectile dysfunction, go the extra mile and thoroughly check out your online facilitator so that you can be assured that you&#8217;re receiving the genuine product and that it is appropriate for your particular needs.</p>
